  "notes": "Kalaallisut (West Greenlandic), the official language of Greenland. The 1973 orthography is essentially phonemic. Three underlying vowels /i u a/; the letters ⟨e⟩ and ⟨o⟩ are not extra phonemes but spell the uvular-lowered allophones of /i/ and /u/ before ⟨r⟩ and ⟨q⟩ — they are given here as [e]/[o] so the surface transcription is right. ⟨r⟩ = /ʁ/, ⟨g⟩ = /ɣ/, ⟨q⟩ = uvular /q/; ⟨ll⟩ = the long voiceless lateral fricative /ɬː/ and ⟨ts⟩ = /tsː/. ⟨ng⟩ = /ŋ/, ⟨rn⟩ = uvular nasal /ɴ/. Doubled letters mark long vowels and geminate consonants; consonant clusters are heavily assimilated in the modern spelling. ⟨f b d h⟩ occur essentially only in loanwords and names.",
